==>STEP NUM: 39
==>ACT: southwest
==>OBSERVATION: Winding Road
The road branches to the northeast and northwest with the lighthouse off to the northwest. To the south is an impenetrable swamp.
Pete the Rat is off to the northwest.
The Weasel is off to the northwest.
Johnny Red is off to the northwest.
===========
==>STEP NUM: 40
==>ACT: northwest
==>OBSERVATION: Winding Road
The road ends at the lighthouse to the north, and heads back to the southeast. You can see and hear the ocean pound the shoreline.
Pete the Rat fiddles with his eyepatch, shifting his weight from foot to foot.
A short, wiry guy known only as "the Weasel" is over in a corner, picking his teeth with a knife.
Johnny Red is here.
Johnny nods, then pulls out a dinner plate he says he came across while on a shark hunt.
